# Windows Development (Solo / Vibe Coding)

**Windows 11** solo developer (Intel Core Ultra 5 125H, 15.6 GB RAM, ~4 GB free). Shell is **PowerShell**, not bash.

## Agent Must Do

- Run terminal commands in **PowerShell 5.1+** syntax — never bash/macOS (`&&`, HEREDOC, `export`, `open`, `pbcopy`, `sed -i ''`).
- Chain commands with `;` not `&&`. Example: `git fetch origin; git rebase origin/main`
- Use `git commit -m "message"` and `gh pr create --body-file path` — no HEREDOC.
- Prefer **Node.js** or `npm run` scripts over shell-specific tooling.
- Be **memory-conscious**: one dev server at a time, no parallel heavy builds.
- Keep **LF line endings** (see `.gitattributes`).

